00:55:30,260 --> 00:55:32,409
Brunches! Don't forget about the
brunches.

1008
00:55:32,510 --> 00:55:36,740
[sobbing] It was a book club
that took my poor Sven!

1009
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:40,119
You see? The postman
and that old toy maker

1010
00:55:40,219 --> 00:55:42,572
are brainwashing everyone!

1011
00:55:42,672 --> 00:55:43,739
What're you saying?

1012
00:55:43,838 --> 00:55:47,713
I'm saying it's time to join forces
against a common enemy.

1013
00:55:50,291 --> 00:55:53,242
I'm saying we need a truce.

1014
00:55:53,342 --> 00:55:56,411
[gasps] A truce? Have you gone mad?

1015
00:55:56,510 --> 00:55:58,949
Either we band together
to take care of this,

1016
00:55:59,050 --> 00:56:00,869
or it's gonna be all book clubs

1017
00:56:00,969 --> 00:56:03,085
- and cookouts from here on...
- [man] And brunches!

1018
00:56:03,186 --> 00:56:06,367
- Don't forget about the brunches.
- Yes, that... that too.

1019
00:56:06,467 --> 00:56:11,780
So, we must join together in peace
to help stop this peace?

1020
00:56:11,880 --> 00:56:15,164
Our ancestors demand it.

1021
00:56:18,125 --> 00:56:20,157
For the Ellingboe bloodline!

1022
00:56:20,257 --> 00:56:22,789
For the Krums' honor.

1023
00:56:23,541 --> 00:56:26,420
The clans are on the warpath...

1024
00:56:27,708 --> 00:56:28,788
together!

1025
00:56:29,416 --> 00:56:31,989
- [all clamoring]
- Mine! Mine! Mine!

1026
00:56:32,088 --> 00:56:33,824
Mine! Mine!

1027
00:56:33,923 --> 00:56:34,923
Mine!

1028
00:56:37,666 --> 00:56:39,867
[all shouting]

1029
00:56:39,967 --> 00:56:41,739
I... [sighs]

1030
00:56:41,840 --> 00:56:45,333
This is gonna take a lot of work.

1031
00:56:46,291 --> 00:56:48,291
- [birds chirping]
- [wood splintering]

1032
00:56:53,291 --> 00:56:54,291
[grunts]

1033
00:56:59,583 --> 00:57:01,003
[chiming]

1034
00:57:47,541 --> 00:57:49,782
- Surprise!
- Oh!

1035
00:57:49,882 --> 00:57:50,882
Jesper?

1036
00:57:50,981 --> 00:57:54,739
- Wha-what are you...
- Welcome to your new workshop!

1037
00:57:54,840 --> 00:57:56,742
- Ta-da!
- What... What is...

1038
00:57:56,842 --> 00:57:59,039
- It'll all be explained in a minute.
- Why did you...

1039
00:57:59,139 --> 00:58:00,898
- I don't want to...
- Come. Sit, sit, sit.

1040
00:58:01,125 --> 00:58:03,157
You'll love this. I promise.

1041
00:58:03,257 --> 00:58:04,257
[clears throat]

1042
00:58:04,356 --> 00:58:05,882
Christmas!

1043
00:58:06,875 --> 00:58:08,320
Christmas? What do you...

1044
00:58:08,420 --> 00:58:12,117
Think about it! Every child in town
gets up on Christmas morning

1045
00:58:12,217 --> 00:58:14,072
and finds a...

1046
00:58:14,172 --> 00:58:17,246
brand-new toy waiting for them
by the fireplace.

1047
00:58:17,750 --> 00:58:19,869
We can make the holiday even more
magical.

1048
00:58:19,969 --> 00:58:21,699
Think of the joy. Think of the
happiness.

1049
00:58:21,798 --> 00:58:23,159
Jesper, listen. I don't think...

1050
00:58:23,260 --> 00:58:24,260
Puh-puh-puh!

1051
00:58:24,358 --> 00:58:26,460
Let me finish. Let me finish.

1052
00:58:27,333 --> 00:58:29,090
Think of all those
happy little faces, huh?

1053
00:58:29,190 --> 00:58:30,739
They're so cute! They're just... Aww!

1054
00:58:30,838 --> 00:58:32,835
- Aren't they so... Look!
- [sighs] Even if we...

1055
00:58:32,936 --> 00:58:34,875
Where are you gonna get that many toys?

1056
00:58:35,375 --> 00:58:36,375
You...

1057
00:58:36,875 --> 00:58:37,954
make new ones!

1058
00:58:41,041 --> 00:58:42,831
I don't make toys.

1059
00:58:44,666 --> 00:58:45,780
Not anymore.

1060
00:58:45,880 --> 00:58:49,115
Pfft. You... You have a gift, my friend.

1061
00:58:49,215 --> 00:58:51,239
Birdhouses are nice and all, but come
on!

1062
00:58:51,340 --> 00:58:52,702
Those hands were meant

1063
00:58:52,802 --> 00:58:54,032
- for making...
- I said no.

1064
00:58:54,132 --> 00:58:56,907
Come on! Work with me here.
Picture the possibilities.

1065
00:58:57,007 --> 00:58:58,572
Look, woodwork would go here.

1066
00:58:58,672 --> 00:58:59,739
- No.
- And here,

1067
00:58:59,838 --> 00:59:01,784
clockwork with all the gears and the
cogs,

1068
00:59:01,884 --> 00:59:03,681
- for you to tinker with all day.
- Stop it.

1069
00:59:03,782 --> 00:59:06,452
And in this corner,
row after row of shiny tools

1070
00:59:06,552 --> 00:59:08,668
- of all shapes and sizes.
- Wait! Don't touch that!

1071
00:59:08,768 --> 00:59:10,503
- Impeccably organized for you!
- No!

1072
00:59:22,833 --> 00:59:23,833
What's this?

1073
00:59:26,041 --> 00:59:27,041
Get out.

1074
00:59:27,416 --> 00:59:28,867
Klaus, I'm sorry.

1075
00:59:28,967 --> 00:59:30,538
- I, I didnt mean...
- Get out!

1076
00:59:32,041 --> 00:59:33,670
[breathing heavily]

1077
00:59:43,250 --> 00:59:44,250
[Klaus sighs]

1078
00:59:59,500 --> 01:00:01,130
[speaking Saami]

1079
01:00:04,750 --> 01:00:06,880
[groans] Bad night, huh?

1080
01:00:07,541 --> 01:00:09,869
Ugh. Well, join the club.

1081
01:00:09,969 --> 01:00:12,409
[speaking Saami]

1082
01:00:12,509 --> 01:00:14,572
Nah, I don't want to bore you with it.

1083
01:00:14,672 --> 01:00:17,076
[speaking Saami]

1084
01:00:17,666 --> 01:00:19,702
Well, okay.
It's just been bothering me, you know?

1085
01:00:19,802 --> 01:00:23,619
If I don't get those letters,
then what am I supposed to do?

1086
01:00:23,719 --> 01:00:25,036
Stay in this little town forever,

1087
01:00:25,137 --> 01:00:27,780
hanging out with an old woodsman,
surrounded by crazy people,

1088
01:00:27,880 --> 01:00:29,534
and never wanting anything more?

1089
01:00:30,416 --> 01:00:31,496
[sighs]

1090
01:00:32,333 --> 01:00:35,411
Back home,
I've got pretty much everything.

1091
01:00:35,510 --> 01:00:36,510
But here...

1092
01:00:37,458 --> 01:00:38,739
I'm just...

1093
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:41,463
another irrelevant, pointless...

1094
01:00:43,416 --> 01:00:44,416
nobody.

1095
01:00:46,375 --> 01:00:49,030
But Klaus, he doesn't deserve...

1096
01:00:49,130 --> 01:00:50,414
I didn't mean to...

1097
01:00:51,125 --> 01:00:53,570
Well, now I just feel like a...
I've behaved like a...

1098
01:00:53,670 --> 01:00:55,117
[speaking Saami]

1099
01:00:55,217 --> 01:00:56,708
- [giggles]
- Precisely.

1100
01:00:57,500 --> 01:01:00,789
Hey. You're a pretty good listener,
you know?

1101
01:01:03,041 --> 01:01:04,159
[sighs]

1102
01:01:04,260 --> 01:01:06,630
All right, you win.

1103
01:01:08,541 --> 01:01:09,670
Let's go. Follow me.

1104
01:01:14,083 --> 01:01:15,492
Sorry to bother you this late, but,

1105
01:01:15,592 --> 01:01:19,043
by any chance, would you happen
to understand... this?

1106
01:01:20,083 --> 01:01:22,132
[speaking Saami]

1107
01:01:25,541 --> 01:01:27,751
Okay. Come in.

1108
01:01:33,333 --> 01:01:35,583
All right. Let's get started.

1109
01:01:36,083 --> 01:01:39,003
- Who wants some hot cocoa?
- [speaking Saami]

1110
01:01:43,000 --> 01:01:44,000
Oh, oh, oh!

1111
01:01:44,099 --> 01:01:45,449
She said she'd like a boat!

1112
01:01:45,548 --> 01:01:47,659
- Really?
- No, that can't be right. Scratch that.

1113
01:01:47,760 --> 01:01:49,572
- [speaking Saami]
- [Alva chuckles]

1114
01:01:49,672 --> 01:01:51,947
- Yes, yes, yes.
- What?

1115
01:01:52,047 --> 01:01:55,170
[chuckles] What're you talking about?
Are you talking about me?

1116
01:01:58,916 --> 01:02:01,239
<i> All I know is </i>

1117
01:02:01,338 --> 01:02:07,784
<i> If happy lives a mile away
A couple steps is all it takes </i>

1118
01:02:07,884 --> 01:02:13,697
<i> If kindness lives in everyone
Then all it takes is standing up </i>

1119
01:02:13,797 --> 01:02:16,701
<i> Can't touch it, see it </i>

1120
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:18,001
<i> Oh </i>

1121
01:02:18,800 --> 01:02:22,992
<i> But you can always feel it </i>

1122
01:02:23,092 --> 01:02:24,291
<i> Oh </i>

1123
01:02:24,969 --> 01:02:31,322
<i> The greatest things you'll ever know </i>

1124
01:02:31,422 --> 01:02:34,746
<i> Are invisible </i>

1125
01:02:56,333 --> 01:02:57,733
[sighs]

1126
01:02:59,916 --> 01:03:01,530
[wood planer grinding]

1127
01:03:01,630 --> 01:03:02,630
Huh?

1128
01:03:20,083 --> 01:03:21,543
- Klaus, I...
- Uh.

1129
01:03:27,291 --> 01:03:32,409
<i> If happy lives a mile away
A couple steps is all it takes </i>

1130
01:03:32,510 --> 01:03:33,510
[chuckles]

1131
01:03:33,608 --> 01:03:39,659
<i> If kindness lives in everyone
Then all it takes is standing up </i>

1132
01:03:39,760 --> 01:03:42,159
<i> Can't touch it, see it </i>

1133
01:03:42,260 --> 01:03:43,282
[whale calls]

1134
01:03:43,382 --> 01:03:44,581
<i> Oh </i>

1135
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:48,820
<i> But you can always feel it </i>

1136
01:03:48,920 --> 01:03:50,121
<i> Oh </i>

1137
01:03:50,967 --> 01:03:57,617
<i> The greatest things you'll ever know </i>

1138
01:03:57,717 --> 01:04:01,038
<i> Are invisible </i>

1139
01:04:07,541 --> 01:04:09,001
[Klaus grunts]

1140
01:04:23,375 --> 01:04:24,375
[gasps]

1141
01:04:24,474 --> 01:04:26,333
[speaking Saami]

1142
01:04:29,666 --> 01:04:31,126
[chuckling]

1143
01:04:32,958 --> 01:04:35,208
- [speaks Saami]
- Oh.

1144
01:04:35,791 --> 01:04:37,751
[parents speaking Saami]

1145
01:04:44,208 --> 01:04:47,449
- [father speaking Saami]
- Whoo-hoo!

1146
01:04:47,548 --> 01:04:48,548
[father] Yoo-hoo!

1147
01:04:48,648 --> 01:04:50,869
<i> Can't touch it, see it </i>

1148
01:04:50,969 --> 01:04:52,168
<i> Oh </i>

1149
01:04:52,840 --> 01:04:55,742
<i> But you can always feel it </i>

1150
01:04:55,842 --> 01:04:57,202
Yoo-hoo!

1151
01:04:57,302 --> 01:04:58,501
<i> Oh </i>

1152
01:04:59,219 --> 01:05:04,409
<i> The greatest things you'll ever know </i>

1153
01:05:04,509 --> 01:05:07,909
<i> Are invisible </i>

1154
01:05:08,090 --> 01:05:10,034
- [father] Yoo!
- [mother laughing]

1155
01:05:10,134 --> 01:05:13,824
<i> They are invisible </i>

1156
01:05:18,750 --> 01:05:23,532
Looks like someone
might need help mailing letters.

1157
01:05:23,632 --> 01:05:24,632
Yeah.

1158
01:05:25,250 --> 01:05:26,572
- Who?
- I, I...

1159
01:05:26,672 --> 01:05:27,672
I mean...

1160
01:05:28,375 --> 01:05:31,074
How have we never defeated you?

1161
01:05:32,083 --> 01:05:33,911
[Jesper] Yeah, then...

1162
01:05:34,010 --> 01:05:37,409
when she got on the sled,
I thought,
"Oh, no! We made it too small."

1163
01:05:37,510 --> 01:05:39,909
But no! It was just right for her size.

1164
01:05:40,010 --> 01:05:41,572
[chuckles] And she loved it, right?

1165
01:05:41,672 --> 01:05:43,570
I think she did.
Do you think she loved it?

1166
01:05:43,670 --> 01:05:44,670
[grunts]

1167
01:05:44,769 --> 01:05:45,952
- I do.
- Yeah.

1168
01:05:46,052 --> 01:05:48,119
Me too. Me too. Yeah, she loved it.

1169
01:05:48,219 --> 01:05:49,409
[chuckles]

1170
01:05:49,509 --> 01:05:55,282
You know, I remember the day I first had
that very same smile on my face.

1171
01:05:55,382 --> 01:06:00,157
What? What smile? I wasn't smiling.
I was squinting. From the sun.

1172
01:06:00,257 --> 01:06:01,329
Right.

1173
01:06:01,833 --> 01:06:03,963
I didn't want to admit it at first
either.

1174
01:06:04,416 --> 01:06:06,407
[chuckles] She used to tease me about
it.

1175
01:06:06,507 --> 01:06:07,507
"She"?

1176
01:06:08,541 --> 01:06:09,880
My Lydia.

1177
01:06:10,666 --> 01:06:14,626
I remember when I found
this spot in the woods that she loved.

1178
01:06:15,541 --> 01:06:18,130
And I built us a house right here.

1179
01:06:20,125 --> 01:06:21,125
Away from it all.

1180
01:06:22,708 --> 01:06:25,208
But it wasn't gonna be
the two of us for long.

1181
01:06:29,958 --> 01:06:30,958
<i>We wanted children.</i>

1182
01:06:32,708 --> 01:06:33,708
<i>Lots of them.</i>

1183
01:06:34,166 --> 01:06:36,617
<i>Running around, laughing,
getting in trouble.</i>

1184
01:06:36,717 --> 01:06:37,717
[both laughing]

1185
01:06:42,458 --> 01:06:43,878
While we waited,

1186
01:06:44,458 --> 01:06:46,128
I started making toys for them.

1187
01:06:46,708 --> 01:06:51,128
And we waited,
and I kept making toys and more toys.

1188
01:06:52,375 --> 01:06:54,092
Oh! Here's another one. What do you
think?

1189
01:06:54,192 --> 01:06:55,494
And we kept waiting,

1190
01:06:56,333 --> 01:06:58,713
but they never came...

1191
01:07:01,666 --> 01:07:02,666
And then...

1192
01:07:05,583 --> 01:07:07,253
she got sick.

1193
01:07:12,458 --> 01:07:15,418
Even now... sometimes...

1194
01:07:16,375 --> 01:07:19,284
it almost feels like she's still...

1195
01:07:23,958 --> 01:07:24,958
[sighs]

1196
01:07:25,291 --> 01:07:28,880
After... After she was gone,

1197
01:07:29,875 --> 01:07:32,284
I... I guess I got lost.

1198
01:07:33,458 --> 01:07:38,628
She loved birds,
so I just kept making birdhouses.

1199
01:07:40,708 --> 01:07:41,708
But then...

1200
01:07:42,208 --> 01:07:43,918
Then you showed up.

1201
01:07:44,583 --> 01:07:49,172
Delivering these toys,
seeing the joy they bring to children,

1202
01:07:49,791 --> 01:07:51,670
I thought I'd never feel this again.

1203
01:07:52,291 --> 01:07:55,331
And I have you to thank for it, my
friend.

1204
01:07:55,916 --> 01:07:57,916
So... thank you.

1205
01:07:59,500 --> 01:08:00,500
Of course.

1206
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:04,210
- Hey, you know what? We're doing it!
- What?

1207
01:08:04,791 --> 01:08:06,451
- Doing what?
- The Christmas thing!

1208
01:08:06,550 --> 01:08:08,242
We're making all those toys!

1209
01:08:08,342 --> 01:08:10,139
- That's what she would've wanted.
- Really?

1210
01:08:10,239 --> 01:08:12,780
Yeah, really!
And with a whole year of planning,

1211
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:15,407
- we can expand to more villages next
year.
- Next year?

1212
01:08:15,507 --> 01:08:17,463
- And more the year after that!
- But I won't...

1213
01:08:17,564 --> 01:08:19,520
I mean, who knows
what's gonna happen next year?

1214
01:08:19,621 --> 01:08:20,621
I might not even...

1215
01:08:20,720 --> 01:08:23,742
[chuckles] What're you going on about?
Let's go! No time to lose!

1216
01:08:23,841 --> 01:08:25,073
[sighs]

1217
01:08:25,173 --> 01:08:26,876
[softly] I might not even be here.

1218
01:08:36,375 --> 01:08:39,819
[children] <i> One, two, three, four,
five </i>

1219
01:08:39,920 --> 01:08:43,570
<i> Once I caught a fish alive </i>

1220
01:08:43,671 --> 01:08:46,956
<i> Six, seven, eight, nine, ten </i>

1221
01:08:47,457 --> 01:08:50,497
<i> Then I let it go again </i>

1222
01:08:51,000 --> 01:08:54,159
<i> Why did you let it go? </i>

1223
01:08:54,260 --> 01:08:57,159
<i> Because it bit my finger so! </i>

1224
01:08:57,260 --> 01:09:00,240
<i> Which finger did it bite? </i>

1225
01:09:00,341 --> 01:09:03,283
<i> This little finger on my right! </i>

1226
01:09:03,384 --> 01:09:04,948
- [Alva] Good job!
- [children] Yay!

1227
01:09:05,047 --> 01:09:06,783
All right, that's it for today.

1228
01:09:06,882 --> 01:09:08,279
And, um... homework!

1229
01:09:08,380 --> 01:09:10,488
Oh! Uh... I forgot about homework.

1230
01:09:10,588 --> 01:09:12,386
- You know what? No homework.
- [boy laughs]

1231
01:09:12,485 --> 01:09:13,884
Am I the best teacher ever or what?

1232
01:09:13,984 --> 01:09:14,984
What...

1233
01:09:15,375 --> 01:09:16,534
- happened here?
- Oh.

1234
01:09:17,250 --> 01:09:20,073
Yeah, I thought
I would give the place an update.

1235
01:09:20,172 --> 01:09:22,658
Everybody knows rotting fish is so over.

1236
01:09:22,757 --> 01:09:24,368
How did you pay for this?

1237
01:09:24,469 --> 01:09:25,469
Hmm?

1238
01:09:25,759 --> 01:09:29,073
- Your savings?
- Well, not all of it.

1239
01:09:29,172 --> 01:09:31,238
Actually, yeah, all of it.
But check it out.

1240
01:09:31,338 --> 01:09:32,497
I think it looks pretty good.

1241
01:09:32,596 --> 01:09:35,659
What about starting
far, far away from here?

1242
01:09:35,760 --> 01:09:36,760
Where's that Alva?

1243
01:09:36,859 --> 01:09:38,742
Someone would have to be pretty stupid

1244
01:09:38,841 --> 01:09:40,599
to want to leave this place now.
[chuckles]

1245
01:09:40,698 --> 01:09:41,789
Don't you think?

1246
01:09:42,500 --> 01:09:44,079
I... guess.

1247
01:09:45,416 --> 01:09:47,279
You guess? Oh, wow.

1248
01:09:47,380 --> 01:09:49,744
You have no idea what you've done, do
you?

1249
01:09:50,250 --> 01:09:52,079
Ugh. Come on. I'll show you.

1250
01:09:58,332 --> 01:10:00,202
Now, would you take a look at that?

1251
01:10:00,301 --> 01:10:02,291
[laughter and indistinct chatter]

1252
